<br>
This is an idea for adding an aspect to the wizard which imho is along the lines of what a wizard is all about. It will at the same time make the wizard more useful in groups, which in these PoP times cant be underestimated. I know we wield much power in short bursts, but what this will add is another more passive ability that would be greatly appreciated in groups. At the same time without stepping on anyones toes as far as I see it. The really great thing about it tho, is that its quite unique and not worth anything solo. <br>
<br>
Now we’re getting to the good part – what am I really talking about heh. Well this ability (or it could be a spell) develops through levels making it better and better. At first its very expensive manawise to utilize, but as one get better it will be gradually cheaper, kinda like canni. I got the idea from one of our only really usable spells atm Spellshield. This one is put on a PC and absorbs magick damage done to that PC. Consider this one now, instead of putting it on a PC you target the mob that does the magick damage (via procs or spells) and activates the skill/spell. Now as the mobs casts say Ice Comet doing those 1120 damage (400 mana), instead of actually causing that damage you interfere and counters it with some amount of mana – say a factor dependent on either hitpoints of damage or manacost of spell. If e.g. manacost dependant it could be with a factor of 3 at a medium level of the CounterMagick skill/spell, costing 1200 mana to counter. This is not very effective manawise, but remember the ratio will get better with higher levels. <br>
<br>
Imagine what a great utility this would be for example to groups trying to down those pesky ocean giants and their darn nukage. With this however those encounters could be balanced far better and made all the more worthwhile for a group. As it is now a single group has more than a handsful trying to down just one of these beasts. It is important to underline that this skill/spell would only be useful to counter magick and as such would only be useful against spellcasting mobs, (and even only if they cause damage possibly (and possibly procs that are spells).)<br>
<br>
If you remember the anchor spell which would prevent a mob from gating out of a fight? This would also have brought something unique to the wizard, and this skill/spell-line is not far from it in usefulness and concept.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I am going to my parent-in-law over the weekend, so feel free to spam me with critique and flames, and yes I admit it, I haven’t checked the board to see if something similar have been posted before heh. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
