<br>
Call it &quot;Casting Slow&quot; or whatever, but when this spell is casted on a target, it actually increases their casting time, allowing you and your friends more time to interrupt.<br>
<br>
The lower level versions could start around +15% increase in casting time on the mob, and at planar levels, it could be around +30%, similar to how spell haste works.<br>
<br>
Tired of getting Ice Cometed in Combat? Toss a spell slow on the mob and Ice Comet now takes 8.2 seconds to cast instead of 6.3. Tired of CHeal mobs healing over and over? Toss a spell slow on the target, and CHeal takes 13 seconds instead of 10.<br>
It gives you more time to toss a stun, or allow your tanks to bash and push the mobs.<br>
<br>
It's not silence, but it's close enough. Unfotunately this would probably fall under chanters, since they're currently the kings of mental debuffs. Oh well. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Jarnin Fisheermann</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
