Yeah I can see the problem with the AE spells, it is however something that could easily be dealt with. 1) Flag AE's as uncounterable 2) Make the cost of countering dependant of damage dealt...whoa...30 targets dealt 800 damage with a counter ratio of e.g. 1 = total cost 24000 mana...yeah right! 3) The very nature of countermagick as I see it is a prospect of countering single target DD's (remember this is meant as having a use in a single group, just like spellshield is cast on the MT to counter the nukermob's nukage), making countering of AE impossible per se. <br>
<br>
The problem with spellshield is that its centered on the MT and wears off rather quickly (low absorption). Countermagick would deal with this, but would at the same time have its costly price in mana. <br>
<br>
At least give us a lvl 65 mother-spellshield then heh with more than a marginal use against something as common as PoP mobs casting Ice Comet. (Instead of a slap in the face with a lvl 65 Greater decession-spell lol.)<br>
