<br>
But I like the idea of being able to diminish another casters damage. Like a reversed Improved Damaged. Decrease Damage spell. First one is -5% damage, second is -10, and so up to -30. We are the masters of damage, so it would work along the lines that we would know how to surpress damage as well. There could even be an AE version, which naturally would effect us if we got hit.<br>
<br>
If something like this every happened, keep in mind, it could be used against us by mobs as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tzarphkaboom>Tzarph Kaboom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/9/03 6:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's a good start</span><hr size=1> Yes, the slow/reduce effect would indeed be fun spell lines by themselves. And to be able to be hit by them ourselves is of course the risk we take by introducing new concepts to the game. <br>
<br>
Concerning the paladin spell, perhaps it would be a matter of tweaking, to make it so that the usefulness of the spell wouldnt be so large as to shutdown each and every spell and proc? Since we are wizards we should only be able to shutdown specific casts of damage spells, or following the lines of other ideas, slowing down the casts to increase possibility of interrupting it, or perhaps a flat out reduction of the damage inflicted. Like chanter/shamans/mages are often called upon to slow attacks, soften targets AC, reduce resists we could receive the power to hit the mob with a spell DD reduction in some way. This would imo bring a deeper aspect to our class than the ordinary nuke, concussion, nuke, concussion etc.etc.<br>
<br>
And btw can you remember the olde idea the developers had about a Translocational Anchor spell for us? Making it so mobs couldnt gate away at all, yet another new concept that didnt make it. <br>
<br>
Just being creative, so many concepts havent been used for classes yet imho. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
